munros.description: A'Bhuidheanach Bheag is a broad, domed summit on the spacious plateau to the east of the Drumochter Pass.
munros.name: A'Bhuidheanach Bheag
munros.region: Loch Ericht to Glen Tromie and Glen Garry

munros.description: A'Chailleach is the westernmost of the Fannichs.
munros.name: A'Chailleach
munros.region: Loch Maree to Loch Broom and Garve

munros.description: Topped by a big cairn, A'Chailleach is the most asceneded and perhaps the finest of the Monadhliath.
munros.name: A'Chailleach (Monadhliath)

munros.description: A'Chraileag is a massive mountain and, despite being lesser known than many of its neighbours, is actually the highest summit in Kintail.
munros.name: A'Chralaig
munros.region: Loch Duich to Loch Ness, South of Loch Mullardoch

munros.description: A'Ghlas-bheinn is a rough and rocky little mountain.
munros.name: A'Ghlas-bheinn
munros.region: Loch Duich to Loch Ness, South of Loch Mullardoch

munros.description: A'Mhaighdean is a magnificent castellated mountain with dramatic cliffs, and one of the finest viewpoints in Britain.
munros.name: A'Mhaighdean
munros.region: Loch Maree to Loch Broom and Garve

munros.description: A'Mharconaich is the most distinctive of the mountains above the Drumochter Pass, showing a steep nose to the northeast.
munros.name: A'Mharconaich
munros.region: Loch Ericht to Glen Tromie and Glen Garry

munros.description: Am Basteir is a vertically-sided blade of rock.
munros.name: Am Basteir

munros.description: Am Bodach is a fine, steep and stony mountain.
munros.name: Am Bodach

munros.description: Am Faochagach is a rounded Munro.
munros.name: Am Faochagach

munros.description: An Caisteal takes the form of a long ridged mountain and its traverse is very enjoyable with interesting features and extensive views over the sea.
munros.name: An Caisteal

munros.description: An Coileachan is the easternmost of the Fannichs, a steep-sided dome rising to the south of Loch Gorm.
munros.name: An Coileachan
munros.region: Loch Maree to Loch Broom and Garve

munros.description: An Gearanach is a magnificent ridge extending north from the main spine of the Mamores.
munros.name: An Gearanach
